        <mxCell id="note_infer" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;rotatable=0;rounded=0;fontSize=11;sketch=1;curveFitting=1;jiggle=2;labelBackgroundColor=none;" value="&lt;b&gt;Real-Time Control (Paper §3.2):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Real observations encoded → attention KV cache (prevents drift)&lt;br&gt;- DiT jointly denoises video + action (coupled in causal self-attn)&lt;br&gt;- Video Head runs but output is discarded (video aids action quality)&lt;br&gt;- 16-step flow sampling; 4 effective DiT forwards (DiT caching)&lt;br&gt;- 7Hz chunk generation; 15Hz action execution (DROID/Franka)&lt;br&gt;- DreamZero-Flash: DiT caching cuts steps; decouple_inference_noise rescales video sigmas to terminate at 0.8 (orthogonal)" vertex="1">
